.TH _PRINTF 3 "APRIL 2024" "Abeer Alsayari" "Custom Printf Manual"
.SH NAME
_printf \- formatted output conversion
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B #include "main.h"
.sp
.BI "int _printf(const char *" format ", ...);"
.SH DESCRIPTION
The \fB_printf\fP function produces output according to a \fIformat\fP as described below. This function was implemented by \fBAbeer Alsayari\fP.
.PP
The function writes the output to \fBstdout\fP, the standard output stream.
.PP
Upon successful return, \fB_printf\fP returns the number of characters printed (excluding the null byte used to end output to strings).
.SH FORMAT SPECIFIERS
The format string is composed of zero or more directives. \fB_printf\fP handles the following conversion specifiers:
.TP
.B c
The \fBint\fP argument is converted to an \fBunsigned char\fP, and the resulting character is written.
.TP
.B s
The \fBconst char *\fP argument is expected to be a pointer to an array of characters (string).
.TP
.B %
A \fB%\fP is written. No argument is converted.
.TP
.B d, i
The \fBint\fP argument is converted to signed decimal notation.
.SH AUTHOR
Written by Abeer Alsayari.
.SH SEE ALSO
printf(3)
